title: Thai Airways resumes twice daily London service
text:
Thai Airways resumes twice daily London service 13 July 2015 Save 
Thai Airways will resume its double-daily London Bangkok service from October 25. 
The airline had suspended night flights when it introduced an A380 to the service from Heathrow at the start of the month. 
However, the introduction of a Boeing 777 on the service, which leaves London at 9.35pm and lands the next day at 4pm, will occur towards the end of October. Return flights will depart Bangkok at 1.20pm, arriving in London at 7.35pm.
